23/02/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Public Order Minister Giorgos Voulgarakis said Wednesday (23 February) that the ministry is working on a new bill aimed at improving crisis management activities.
Voulgarakis described the current system as "fragmented", and said one of the main goals of the project is to establish a new panel to co-ordinate security measures in situations ranging from natural disasters to terror threats.
(Kathimerini - 23/02/05)
